                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>\n                                        <date>25 August 1850</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <placeName>Phila</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My Dr Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I find by one of the Occidents<lb/> recd from you\n                                        by <persName>Simmonds</persName> that you had returned<lb/>\n                                        from <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>—I have not received\n                                        my pack nor<lb/> the small catechisms wrote for let me ask\n                                        you to<lb/> look after it. I requested you to subscribe to\n                                        the<lb/> Asmoneon for me pray let me know if you have<lb/>\n                                        done os, if inconvenient I will apply to <persName>Mr\n                                                  Isaac's</persName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am glad to find that your Congregation<lb/> is\n                                        indisposed to lose your valuable &amp; long services<lb/> I\n                                        trust you will come to an understanding</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Government has made a stir of our having<lb/> a\n                                        Minister which I think the congregation will be<lb/> obliged\n                                        to listen to; left to them, their children<lb/> would grow\n                                        up in complete ignorance, as we have<lb/> no person\n                                        competent to teach the Hebrew, they have<lb/> gone back\n                                        sadly since <persName>Mr Nathans</persName> departure,\n                                        I<lb/> have done all I could to get one, but what can<lb/>\n                                        one do against a <add>?</add>, the danger to the\n                                        congregation<lb/> is imminent for already some of the\n                                        children are<lb/> going to a Christian clergyman's school\n                                        while the<lb/> Lutheran, Protestant, &amp; Dutch Reformed\n                                        Parsons<lb/> have formed a union for distributing\n                                                  <sic>trachs</sic><lb/> which they send from house\n                                        to house.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3348h27t/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
