                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3348h27t/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>see how exposed we are, all for the sake of a<lb/> few\n                                                  dollars—<sic>wont</sic> you say something on\n                                        it—</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I regret to add that my Son\n                                                  <persName>Jacob</persName> arrived<lb/> from\n                                                  <placeName>Panama</placeName> in a deplorable\n                                        state of illness he<lb/> is a trifling better, but doubt if\n                                        he will ever<lb/> become a sound man</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">With best wishes I rem Dr Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">yours truly <persName role=\"author\">A\n                                                  Wolff</persName></p>\n                              <p>the congregation can <sic>will</sic> pay for a minister for<lb/>\n                                        the members are better off than they were 2 years ago.<lb/>\n                                        the children have forgotten all that <persName>Mr\n                                                  Nathan</persName> taught,<lb/> nay very few can\n                                        say <del>then</del> a word of Hebrew &amp; if it continues, the<lb/>\n                                        <del>lang Hebrew</del> language will be entirely lost, many\n                                        young men called<lb/> to the law cannot repeat the blessing\n                                        we are going back<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> to when <persName>Mr Carillon</persName> found\n                                        us—the Sunday School<lb/> has also falling off exceedingly\n                                        only 40 at present of<lb/> which 14 are my nieces nephews\n                                        &amp; grand children, <add>?</add> as to the<lb/> state of\n                                        elementary schooling in the poor children it is<lb/>\n                                        deplorable, nor will any join me in the <sic>expence</sic>\n                                        of<lb/> instructing them do say something on it—the\n                                        congregation<lb/> has no greater opponent than your friend\n                                                  <persName>Simmonds</persName><lb/> whose hatred\n                                        &amp; malice of me instigates him to oppose<lb/> every thing\n                                        good that I propose, you will think it</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3348h27t/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
